name: SYC 03: CL Listings Emails → Listing URLs

parameters.jsonOutput:
={
  "id_email": "{{ $('Not in DB').item.json.id_email }}",
  "city": "{{ $('Not in DB').item.json.city }}",
  "subject": "{{ $('Not in DB').item.json.subject }}",
  "alert_email_received": "{{ $('Not in DB').item.json.alert_email_received }}",
  "listing_url": "{{ $('Not in DB').item.json.listing_url }}",
  "listing_id": "{{ $('Not in DB').item.json.listing_id }}"
}

categories.description: =Email alerts containing (cars+trucks) in  {{ $('Sergios Gmail').first().json.headers.subject }} or containing "CL Search Alerts" <alerts@alerts.craigslist.org> in {{ $json.headers.from }}
Emails that contain the phrase "craigslist login link" and does not contain "cars+trucks" in the {{ $('Sergios Gmail').first().json.headers.subject }}

Email communications from platform tools like Google apps, chatgpt, Sendbird, Textline, n8n, twilio, puppeteer, pinecone, Baserow, Rag, Google Cloud, Azure, AWS, Neo4j or brightdata.com. Also, emails coming from sergio@sellyourcar.ai and any email that was not classified in other group. This is a catch all group.
All other emails not previously categorized

options.systemPromptTemplate:
=Please classify the text provided by the user into one of the following categories: 
- cL_Listings, 
- cL_login_links,
- sys_alerts,
- receipts, 
- tools, 
- other 

Don't explain, and only output the json.
